# navigateForward(to:)

**Instance Method**

Navigates to the specific object.

## Declaration

```swift
@MainActor func navigateForward(to object: Any)
```

## Parameters

- **object**: The object to display.

## Discussion

Clears the [doc://com.apple.appkit/documentation/AppKit/NSPageController/arrangedObjects] array after the selected index, adds the argument to that array, and sets the [doc://com.apple.appkit/documentation/AppKit/NSPageController/selectedIndex] to the object’s index.

## Related Documentation

- **takeSelectedIndexFrom(_:)**: Navigates to the selected index, which is taken from the sender.
- **navigateBack(_:)**: Navigates backwards in the page controller’s arranged objects array.
- **navigateForward(_:)**: Navigates to the next object in the page controller’s arranged objects array, if appropriate.

## Page Controller Items

- **arrangedObjects**: An array containing the objects displayed in the page controller’s view.
- **selectedIndex**: The currently selected object in the arranged objects array.
